parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine oil system failure can cause engine damage, seizure, or failure, leading to costly repairs, accidents, or strandings.
Ignition coil failure can cause engine misfires, stalling, or failure, leading to accidents, strandings, or engine damage.
Radiator fan failure can cause overheating, engine damage, or fires, leading to accidents, strandings, or costly repairs.
Transmission problems can cause erratic shifting, stalling, or failure, leading to accidents, strandings, or costly repairs.
Exhaust system failure can cause strong odors, exhaust fumes entering the vehicle, or accidents.
symptoms: exhaust fumes entering the vehicle through the air intake.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning seat heater can cause a fire in the vehicle, potentially leading to injuries, damage to the vehicle, and even fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Heated Seat Failure and Fire Hazard
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heated seat can cause a fire, resulting in damage to the vehicle and potentially causing injuries to occupants.
symptoms: burning the seat cover and potentially causing injury to occupants
a hole is burned through the seat from underneath

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sliding door latch to engage or lock/unlock at low temperatures can lead to the door opening while driving, creating a safety hazard for occupants and other vehicles, as well as increasing the risk of theft or vandalism when parked.
symptoms: The sliding door latch fails to engage or lock/unlock
the door swings open while driving
the exterior handle sticks and does not operate
the door latch only works when the temperature rises or after parking in a heated garage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can lead to a loss of occupant restraint, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle breaks into several pieces
the seat belt will not connect to the base buckle housing
the passenger seat belt locks up and does not extend
the seat belt makes a whirring sound when pulled out
the seat belt requires repeated attempts to function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to lock up, making it difficult or impossible to use, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt locks up and does not extend
the seat belt makes a whirring sound when pulled out
the seat belt requires repeated attempts to function properly.
